<div class="SpellDiv" style="float:left; width:500px;">
<div class='heading'><P>Detect Scrying</p></div><P class='SPDet'><b>School</b> divination; <B>Level</b> bard 4, sorcerer/wizard 4, witch 4, inquisitor 4, shaman 4</p><div class='Sep1'>Casting</div><P class='SPDet'><b>Casting Time</b> 1 standard action</p><P class='SPDet'><b>Components</b> V, S, M (a piece of mirror and a miniature brass hearing trumpet)</p><div class='Sep1'>Effect</div><P class='SPDet'><b>Range</b> 40 ft.</p><P class='SPDet'><b>Area</b> 40-ft.-radius emanation centered on you</p><P class='SPDet'><b>Duration</b> 24 hours</p><P class='SPDet'><b>Saving Throw</b> none; <b>Spell Resistance</b> no</p><div class='Sep1'>Description</div><div class='SPDesc'><p>You immediately become aware of any attempt to observe you by means of a divination (scrying) spell or effect. The spell's area radiates from you and moves as you move. You know the location of every magical sensor within the spell's area.</p><p>If the scrying attempt originates within the area, you also know its location; otherwise, you and the scrier immediately make opposed caster level checks (1d20 + caster level). If you at least match the scrier's result, you get a visual image of the scrier and an accurate sense of his direction and distance from you.</p></div>
</div>
